org.apache.ambari.server.api.query.render

Interface Renderer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AlertSummaryGroupedRenderer, AlertSummaryRenderer, BaseRenderer, ClusterBlueprintRenderer, DefaultRenderer, HostKerberosIdentityCsvRenderer, MetricsPaddingRenderer, MinimalRenderer

    public interface Renderer
    Responsible for the rendering of a result. This includes both the content (which properties), and the format of the query result. Format doesn't refer to json or xml, but instead to the structure of the categories, sub-resources and properties. Renderer's are registered for a resource type by adding them to the corresponding resource definition.

      • finalizeProperties

        TreeNode<Set<String>> finalizeProperties(TreeNode<QueryInfo> queryProperties,
                                         boolean isCollection)
        Finalize which properties are requested by the query. This is called once per user query regardless of how many sub-queries the original query is decomposed into.
        Parameters:
        queryProperties - tree of query information. Contains query information for the root query and all sub-queries (children)
        isCollection - whether the query is a collection
        Returns:
        tree of sets of string properties for each query including any sub-queries

      • finalizeResult

        Result finalizeResult(Result queryResult)
        Finalize the query results.
        Parameters:
        queryResult - result of query in native (default) format
        Returns:
        result in the format dictated by the renderer

      • getResultPostProcessor

        ResultPostProcessor getResultPostProcessor(Request request)
        Obtain the associated post processor. Post Processors existed prior to renderer's to allow the native result to be augmented before returning it to the user. This functionality should be merged into the renderer.
        Parameters:
        request - original request
        Returns:
        associated post processor

      • requiresPropertyProviderInput

        boolean requiresPropertyProviderInput()
        Obtains the property provider requirements of the given renderer implementation.
        Returns:
        true if property provider support is required false if property provider support is not required
